<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8073016>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Arethaea solterae sp. nov. (holotype male INHS-P2190-1). A, Wings. B, Thorax and abdomen with interpretation of internal structures. C, Metatibiae and metatarsi.Abbreviations: ag, accessory glands; fb, fat body; tes, testis; txm, thoracic muscles; vt, ventriculus (anterior midgut)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8073016/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

